Sure, here are some example sentences that use the Serbian word "gubljenje" in different forms and positions:

1. Nije dobro *gubiti* vreme na beskorisne stvari. (It's not good to *lose* time on useless things.)
2. Često se žalimo na *gubljenje* novca, ali malo radimo na tome da ga uštedimo. (We often complain about *losing* money, but we don't do much to save it.)
3. Ukoliko želite izbeći *gubljenje* vremena na nepotrebnim aktivnostima, napravite plan za svoj dan. (If you want to avoid *losing* time on unnecessary activities, make a plan for your day.)
4. Njegova *gubljenja* lopti u poslednjoj utakmici koštala su ekipu pobede. (His *loss* of balls in the last game cost the team the victory.)
5. Ponekad je *gubljenje* bitke bolja opcija od nepotrebnog krvoprolića. (Sometimes *losing* the battle is a better option than unnecessary bloodshed.)
6. Kako bismo sprečili *gubljenje* podataka, redovno pravimo sigurnosne kopije. (To prevent *losing* data, we regularly make backups.)

I hope this helps! Let me know if you have any questions.